claim.claim-text:
1. A method for displaying multicast streams, the method comprising:
receiving a first request to subscribe to a first multicast stream being transmitted in a network;
responsive to receiving the first request, registering to receive the first multicast stream and a preview multicast stream, wherein the preview multicast stream includes interleaved frames of pre-recorded content from a plurality of distinct multicast streams, including the first multicast stream;
based on the registering, receiving the first multicast stream and the preview multicast stream from a first-hop router;
storing the preview multicast stream in a cache;
displaying the first multicast stream and the preview multicast stream;
receiving a second request to subscribe to a second multicast stream included in the plurality of distinct multicast streams associated with the preview multicast stream, wherein the second multicast stream is selected based on a selection of frames of the second multicast stream that are displayed as part of the preview multicast stream;
responsive to receiving the second request, reconstructing pre-recorded content of the second multicast stream using the frames of the second multicast stream that are included in the preview multicast stream;
displaying the pre-recorded content of the second multicast stream while registering to receive fresh content of the second multicast stream;
based on the registering, receiving fresh content of the second multicast stream from the first hop router; and
displaying the fresh content of the second multicast stream.

12. A method for distributing multicast streams, the method comprising:
receiving, at an edge site in a network, a first multicast stream from a first source node in the network and a second multicast stream from a second source node in the network;
receiving, at the edge site, a preview multicast stream from the first source node, wherein the preview multicast stream includes interleaved frames of pre-recorded content from a plurality of distinct multicast streams, including the first multicast stream and the second multicast stream;
storing, at the edge site, the first and the second multicast streams and the preview multicast stream;
receiving, at the edge site, a request from a first-hop router to receive the first multicast stream, wherein the first-hop router is associated with a receiving node that is subscribing to the first multicast stream; and
responsive to receiving the request, sending to the first-hop router, using the edge site, the first multicast stream and the preview multicast stream.

